The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Mobile phone user base swells

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Aug. 24: More than two lakh mobile phone customers were added daily in July. According to latest industry data, the mobile phone subscriber base swelled by 8.06 million during the month.

 With this, the total number of telephone subscribers has reached 232.87 million. One in every 20 persons now owns a telephone, said analysts. 

 The telecom subscriber base was 225.01 million in June 2007. 

 The total number of wireless subscribers, including GSM, CDMA and WLL has gone up to 192.98 million at the end of July, a Telecom Regulatory Authority of India report said. The landline subscriber base declined 0.20 million in July to stand at 39.89 million. 




